## Development Sequence

Build in this exact order to ensure each layer is testable before the next is added:

1. **Monorepo scaffold** — set up the workspace, install dependencies, configure TypeScript paths, create the shared types package.

2. **Database migrations** — run all three migrations against a local Supabase instance. Verify the journal balance trigger works by attempting to post an unbalanced entry.

3. **Auth and household setup** — implement signup, login, household creation, and member invitation. Verify RLS is working correctly.

4. **Plaid integration** — implement Link token creation, token exchange, and the plaid-webhook Edge Function. Test in Plaid sandbox. Verify transactions are converting to correct double-entry journal entries.

5. **Calculate-position Edge Function** — implement and test against sandbox data. Connect to the dashboard hero card.

6. **Obligation library and daily accrual scheduler** — implement the obligations UI and the run-daily-accruals Edge Function. Manually trigger the function and verify accrual journal entries post correctly.

7. **Manual entry and document upload** — implement the manual entry form and the parse-document Edge Function. Test with real PDF bank statement samples.

8. **Period close** — implement the close ritual UI and Edge Function. Verify balance sheet snapshots are taken and equity rolls correctly.

9. **Notification system** — wire up in-app Realtime notifications first, then email via Resend, then Web Push.

10. **Charts and historical views** — implement all chart components once there is real data to visualize.

