## Notes for the Developer

- The double-entry balance trigger is the most critical piece of infrastructure. Test it exhaustively before building anything on top of it.
- Never mutate account balances directly. All balance changes must flow through journal entries. Account balances are derived from the ledger, not stored independently (or if cached for performance, always reconciled against the ledger).
- The Plaid access token must never be exposed to the frontend. All Plaid API calls must go through Edge Functions or API routes server-side.
- Row Level Security must be verified independently of application-layer auth. Test direct database queries with different user tokens to confirm isolation.
- The period close is irreversible by design. Add a confirmation modal with explicit user acknowledgment before executing.
- All monetary arithmetic must use integer cents internally to avoid floating point errors. Store as `numeric(12,2)` in PostgreSQL and handle rounding explicitly in application code.
